Social Media Do's & Don'ts for College Students

Do's:
* Audit your privacy settings regularly to control who sees your personal posts.
* Use a professional headshot and a clean bio on platforms like LinkedIn and GitHub.
* Fact-check information before sharing news or technical resources with your peers.
* Give credit to original creators when sharing code, designs, or articles.
* Network meaningfully by sending personalized notes when connecting with professionals.

Don'ts:
* Don't post confidential academic info, such as exam papers or internal VIT notices.
* Don't engage in online arguments or "trolling" that could be traced back to you.
* Don't post unprofessional photos that you wouldn't want a future employer to see.
* Don't overshare your location or real-time schedule for personal safety.
* Don't use offensive language or symbols, even in "private" group chats.
